TITLE: Implementing Custom Tools for Cloudflare Agents
DESCRIPTION: Examples of defining tools for a Cloudflare Agent using the tool builder. Includes patterns for tools that require confirmation, auto-executing tools, and a scheduling tool implementation with different timing patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fiberplane/fiberplane/blob/main/examples/simple-agent/README.md#2025-04-14_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Example of a tool that requires confirmation
const searchDatabase = tool({
  description: "Search the database for user records",
  parameters: z.object({
    query: z.string(),
    limit: z.number().optional(),
  }),
  // No execute function = requires confirmation
});

// Example of an auto-executing tool
const getCurrentTime = tool({
  description: "Get current server time",
  parameters: z.object({}),
  execute: async () => new Date().toISOString(),
});

// Scheduling tool implementation
const scheduleTask = tool({
  description:
    "schedule a task to be executed at a later time. 'when' can be a date, a delay in seconds, or a cron pattern.",
  parameters: z.object({
    type: z.enum(["scheduled", "delayed", "cron"]),
    when: z.union([z.number(), z.string()]),
    payload: z.string(),
  }),
  execute: async ({ type, when, payload }) => {
    // ... see the implementation in tools.ts
  },
});
```

