TITLE: Calculating Uptime Percentages with Hono and Drizzle ORM in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code implements an endpoint to calculate uptime percentages for a given website over a specified time period. It uses SQL date handling and filters checks within the time period, then calculates the percentage by dividing successful checks by total checks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fiberplane/fiberplane/blob/main/www/src/content/blog/2024-12-17-honc-uptime-monitor.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
app.get("/websites/:id/uptime", async (c) => {
  const { id } = c.req.param();
  const days = c.req.query("days") ?? 7;
  const db = drizzle(c.env.DB);

  const startDate = new Date();
  startDate.setDate(startDate.getDate() - days);

  const checks = await db
    .select()
    .from(schema.uptimeChecks)
    .where(
      and(
        eq(schema.uptimeChecks.websiteId, id),
        sql`${schema.uptimeChecks.timestamp} >= ${startDate.toISOString()}`
      )
    );

  const upCount = checks.filter((check) => check.isUp).length;
  const uptimePercentage = (upCount / checks.length) * 100;

  return c.json({
    uptimePercentage: Math.round(uptimePercentage * 100) / 100,
    period: `${days} days`
  });
});
```

