TITLE: Understanding Hono's Context Type Definition
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the structure of Hono's Context type definition with its generic parameters. The Context object is central to Hono's middleware system, providing access to environment variables, request/response objects, and type-safe data sharing between middleware and handlers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fiberplane/fiberplane/blob/main/www/src/content/blog/2025-02-04-hono-validation-middleware.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export type Context<
  // We'll get to these type parameters in a moment
  E extends Env = any,
  P extends string = any,
  I extends Input = {}
> = {
  // Env vars and Cloudflare bindings
  env: E["Bindings"];
  // Augmented Request with optionally-validated data
  get req(): HonoRequest<P, I["out"]>;
  get res(): Response;
  // ...
};
```

