TITLE: Defining Rich-Text Formatting Data Structures in Rust
DESCRIPTION: The data structure used by Fiberplane to represent rich text formatting. It consists of a vector of AnnotationWithOffset objects, where each annotation represents a formatting instruction like bold or italics with an associated offset position.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fiberplane/fiberplane/blob/main/www/src/content/blog/2024-02-26-a-deep-dive-into-fiberplane's-operational-transformation.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
type Formatting = Vec<AnnotationWithOffset>;

struct AnnotationWithOffset {
    annotation: Annotation,
    offset: u32,
}

enum Annotation {
    StartBold,
    EndBold,
    StartItalics,
    EndItalics,
    StartLink { url: String },
    EndLink,
    /* more like these... */
}
```

