TITLE: Importing Deserialized Values from WebAssembly Host in Rust
DESCRIPTION: A Rust function that deserializes data from a fat pointer provided by the host (TypeScript). It handles the conversion from serialized data in WebAssembly memory to a Rust type and then frees the allocated memory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fiberplane/fiberplane/blob/main/www/src/content/blog/2022-02-18-How-to-pass-rich-data-types-between-TypeScript-And-A-Rust-WebAssembly-Module.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[doc(hidden)]
pub unsafe fn import_value_from_host<'de, T: Deserialize<'de>>(fat_ptr: FatPtr) -> T {
    let (ptr, len) = from_fat_ptr(fat_ptr);
    if len & 0xff000000 != 0 {
        panic!("Unknown extension bits");
    }

    let slice = std::slice::from_raw_parts(ptr, len as usize);
    let mut deserializer = Deserializer::new(slice).with_human_readable();
    let value = T::deserialize(&mut deserializer).unwrap();

    __fp_free(fat_ptr);

    value
}
```

